<h2>Common Mistakes We Help You Avoid</h2>
<p>Executors and administrators often make costly errors without proper legal guidance. These include distributing assets before all debts and taxes are settled, failing to advertise the estate or notify creditors, missing the inheritance tax filing deadline, paying claims out of priority order, and failing to obtain proper releases from beneficiaries before distribution. Personal liability for these mistakes can fall directly on the executor.</p>
